results:
Based on the search results, Dune: Part One (2021) earned $400.7 million worldwide at the box office. The film had a production budget of $165 million, making it a commercial success that helped secure the production of its sequel.

The movie was released in October 2021 and despite being released simultaneously on HBO Max in the United States, it performed well enough globally to justify continuing the franchise with Dune: Part Two.
